<PageLayout
  title="Privacy Tips"
  eyebrow="Privacy Hub"
  heading="Privacy Tips"
  intro="Small habits that make a big difference for your online privacy."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1496180470114-6ef490f3ff22?w=1600&q=80&auto=format&fit=crop"
>
  <h2>On Duncit</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Turn on two-factor authentication in Settings → Security.</li>
    <li>Review your visibility — choose who can see your profile and when.</li>
    <li>Don't put your last name, school, or workplace in your bio.</li>
    <li>Use the in-app camera; uploaded photos can carry GPS metadata.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Everywhere else</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Use a password manager. Long, unique passwords for every site.</li>
    <li>Enable 2FA wherever it's offered.</li>
    <li>Be suspicious of unsolicited links, even from people you know.</li>
    <li>Review app permissions on your phone monthly.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>If you're being harassed</h2>
  <p>Document everything (screenshots), block the person, report to Duncit, and reach out to <a href="/safety/resources">these resources</a>. You're not alone.</p>
</PageLayout>
